`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The two-tier loot test design is worth noting: `rollLoot(tableId, tier, rng)` is tested with an explicit RNG object (pure unit test), while `rollLootForEnemy(enemyId, tableId, tier, worldSeed)` tests the seeded wrapper separately. This separation means you can always test the core algorithm in isolation, and the scoped-seed contract is tested as a thin layer on top — easy to debug either half independently.
